Inflict 3 mortal damage on the target.
**^^Spell^^**, **^^Unlimited^^**
Your Hero Phase
Pick a friendly **^^Slaves to Darkness Wizard^^** to cast this spell, pick a visible enemy unit within 12" of them to be the target, then make a casting roll of 2D6.
The target has **^^Strike-last^^** until the start of your next turn.
Your Hero Phase

Pick a friendly **^^Slaves to Darkness Wizard^^** to cast this spell, pick a visible friendly **^^Slaves to Darkness^^** unit wholly within 12" of them to be the target, then make a casting roll of 2D6.
For the rest of the turn, add 1 to the number of dice rolled when making charge rolls for the target, to a maximum of 3.
Subtract 5 from the control scores of enemy **^^Infantry^^** units while they are in combat with this unit.
Once Per Battle, Your Hero Phase
Pick a terrain feature within 12" of this unit to be the target.

If the target does not have the ‘Obscuring’ terrain ability, it gains that ability until the start of your next turn. Then, roll a dice for each model (friendly and enemy) within 1" of the target. For each 5+, inflict 1 mortal damage on that model’s unit.
Pick a visible enemy **^^Wizard^^** within 24" of this unit to be the target.

For the rest of the turn, each time the target is picked to use a **^^Spell^^** ability, inflict D3 mortal damage on the target as a reaction. If the target is destroyed by this ability, do not resolve the effect of that **^^Spell^^** ability.
Once Per Turn (Army), Your Movement Phase
If there is a friendly **^^Darkoath Hero^^** on the battlefield, pick a friendly non-**^^Hero^^** non-**^^Unique Darkoath^^** unit that has been destroyed to be the target.

Roll a dice. On a 3+, set up a replacement unit with half the number of models from the target unit (rounding up) on the battlefield, wholly within 6" of a battlefield edge and more than 3" from all enemy units.

While there is at least 1 friendly **^^Warriors of Chaos Hero^^** and 1 other friendly **^^Daemon Hero^^** or **^^Darkoath Hero^^** on the battlefield, add 2 to the control scores of friendly **^^Slaves to Darkness^^** units while they are contesting an objective that is wholly outside friendly territory.
Once Per Turn (Army), Reaction: You declared a **^^Fight^^** ability for a friendly **Daemon Prince** unit
The **Daemon Prince** unit using that **^^Fight^^** ability.

Pick a friendly non-**^^Hero Slaves to Darkness Monster^^** or **^^Beast^^** unit that has not used a **^^Fight^^** ability this turn and is wholly within 12" of this unit to be the target. The target can be picked to use a **^^Fight^^** ability immediately after the **^^Fight^^** ability used by this unit has been resolved.
Once Per Turn (Army), End of Any Turn
Pick an objective that is contested by any friendly units to be the target.

Place a **defiled token** next to the target objective. Then, roll a D3 for each enemy unit contesting an objective that has a **defiled token**. On a 2+, inflict an amount of mortal damage on that enemy unit equal to the roll.
Deployment Phase
This unit can use the ‘Eye of the Gods’ ability as if it were the end of the turn and it had destroyed an enemy unit this turn.
Once Per Battle, Any Combat Phase
This unit can use 2 **^^Fight^^** abilities this phase. After the first is used, however, this unit has **^^Strike-last^^** for the rest of the turn.
Any Hero Phase
Pick each damaged friendly unit wholly within 12" of this unit to be the targets.
Roll a dice for each target. On a 3+, **Heal (1)** the target. **Heal (3)** the target instead if it is a Monster.
Your Hero Phase
If there is not a friendly **Darkfire Daemonrift** on the battlefield, pick a friendly **^^Slaves to Darkness Wizard^^** to cast this spell, then make a casting roll of 2D6.
Set up a **^^Darkfire Daemonrift^^** wholly within 12" of the caster, visible to them and more than 9" from all enemy units.
Your Hero Phase
If there is not a friendly *:Eightfold Doom-Sigil** on the battlefield, pick a friendly **^^Slaves to Darkness Wizard^^** to cast this spell, then make a casting roll of 2D6.
If there is not a friendly **Eightfold Doom-Sigil** on the battlefield, pick a friendly **^^Slaves to Darkness Wizard^^** to cast this spell, then make a casting roll of 2D6.
Your Hero Phase
If there is not a friendly **Realmscourge Rupture** on the battlefield, pick a friendly **^^Slaves to Darkness Wizard^^** to cast this spell, then make a casting roll of 2D6.
Set up a **Realmscourge Rupture** wholly within 12" of the caster, visible to them and more than 9" from all enemy units.

Friendly Slaves to Darkness units have 1 of the following effects based on the Mark of Chaos keyword they have.
• **^^Undivided:^^** Add 1 to wound rolls for the unit’s combat attacks that target a **^^Hero^^** or **^^Monster^^**.
• **^^Khorne:^^** Add 1 to the Attacks characteristic of the unit’s melee weapons for the rest of the turn if the unit charged in the same turn.
• **^^Tzeentch:^^** The unit has **^^Ward (4+)^^** against mortal damage inflicted by **^^Spell^^** abilities and abilities used by **^^Manifestations^^**.
• **^^Nurgle:^^** Subtract 1 from wound rolls for combat attacks that target the unit.
• **^^Slaanesh:^^** Add 1 to run rolls and charge rolls for the unit. If a unit with a Mark of Chaos keyword is replaced, the replacement unit has the same Mark of Chaos keyword.
Once Per Turn, End of Any Turn
Each friendly **^^Slaves to Darkness^^** unit that destroyed an enemy unit this turn is a target. Friendly **^^Beasts^^** and non-**^^Hero Monsters^^** cannot be targeted by this ability.

Make a reward roll of D6 for each target and apply the corresponding effect below. You can re-roll the reward roll for the target, but if you do so and you roll a 1, inflict D3 mortal damage on the target.
**1 *Snubbed by the Gods:*** No effect.
**2 *Mutative Regrowth:*** **Heal (3)** the target.
**3 *Unnatural Grace:*** Add 1 to hit rolls for the target’s combat attacks for the rest of the battle.
**4 *Lurid Aura:*** The target has **^^Ward (6+)^^** for the rest of the battle. If the target already has **^^Ward (6+)^^**, it has **^^Ward (5+)^^** instead.
**5 *Slaughterer’s Might:*** Add 1 to the Rend characteristic of the target’s melee weapons for the rest of the battle.
**6 *Champion of Chaos:*** Pick any other effect.
The same effect can be applied multiple times to a unit, and more than 1 effect can apply to a unit at the same time.
